cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.CE, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving user experience and productivity for building maintenance staff and regular users of vertical transportation facilities. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper discusses the impact of technology on building maintenance and user experience. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper describes the development of a web-based system for vertical transportation. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) could be relevant as the paper involves the analysis of data collected from vertical transport facilities. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could also be relevant as the paper discusses the use of technology to improve communication and collaboration between building maintenance staff and users of vertical transportation facilities.
